<div id="review_947628281" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/947628281" />
    <a title="Dawn" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8379936-dawn"><img alt="Dawn" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1332684630p2/8379936.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/947628281?book_show_action=true">May 25, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dawn" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dawn" href="/user/show/8379936-dawn">Dawn</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer947628281" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14442839050862405038">When I say this book is brilliant, I do not mean it in the British sense, as in casually cool, nice job, well done... I mean it is insightful, creative, well-written, highly developed characters and an incredible story line. Just when you think it cannot get any better, it does! And, which I love, is it makes you really think about thinks like societal expectations of women, good versus evil, and right/wrong. I haven&apos;t ripped through a book like this in years, and I loved every second of this bo</span>
  <span id="freeText14442839050862405038" style="display:none">When I say this book is brilliant, I do not mean it in the British sense, as in casually cool, nice job, well done... I mean it is insightful, creative, well-written, highly developed characters and an incredible story line. Just when you think it cannot get any better, it does! And, which I love, is it makes you really think about thinks like societal expectations of women, good versus evil, and right/wrong. I haven't ripped through a book like this in years, and I loved every second of this book. Wonderful.... I can see why they made it into a movie (highly underrated, I might add). And I propose a re-make, one that fleshes out Ruth in more depth than the fluffy 80's version. She is, and does, so much more - ah, but that is always true of novels. Must read!</span>
  <a data-text-id="14442839050862405038" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


