    </div>
  </div>
    <div class="elementListBrownSeparator"></div>



  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_32143957" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/32143957" />
    <a title="Alia" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/253804-alia"><img alt="Alia" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1607281894p2/253804.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/32143957?book_show_action=true">Sep 05, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Alia" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Alia" href="/user/show/253804-alia">Alia</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780345323750" href="/book/show/815492.The_Life_and_Loves_of_a_She_Devil">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer32143957" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9208584035549765885">This book was unbelievably shallow, mean, and petty, and I did not enjoy it at all. At first you sort of feel sorry for the main character, Ruth, because her husband cheats on her and essentially blames her for all of their problems. But her idea of revenge is to not only destroy the life of her husband&apos;s mistress, but to then take over that life. She becomes a horrible person who does far worse things than the mistress ever did, and we&apos;re supposed to still care about her and empathize with her?</span>
  <span id="freeText9208584035549765885" style="display:none">This book was unbelievably shallow, mean, and petty, and I did not enjoy it at all. At first you sort of feel sorry for the main character, Ruth, because her husband cheats on her and essentially blames her for all of their problems. But her idea of revenge is to not only destroy the life of her husband's mistress, but to then take over that life. She becomes a horrible person who does far worse things than the mistress ever did, and we're supposed to still care about her and empathize with her? No, I don't think so. I would not recommend this book to anyone.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9208584035549765885" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

