              <span id="reviewTextContainer2237235406" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12698370478885143297">This is a subversive revenge tale because the desire for revenge is shown for the twisted envy that can develop for the target of the revenge. This is touted as a feminist revenge tale, but it is more of a subtle critique than the bludgeon I have seen it reviewed as. Feminism is critiqued. Men are critiqued. Religion is critiqued. Government, plastic surgeons, feminist communes, the poor -- no one comes out unscathed. Not to mention romance novels. The interesting thing is I didn&apos;t fully realize</span>
  <span id="freeText12698370478885143297" style="display:none">This is a subversive revenge tale because the desire for revenge is shown for the twisted envy that can develop for the target of the revenge. This is touted as a feminist revenge tale, but it is more of a subtle critique than the bludgeon I have seen it reviewed as. Feminism is critiqued. Men are critiqued. Religion is critiqued. Government, plastic surgeons, feminist communes, the poor -- no one comes out unscathed. Not to mention romance novels. The interesting thing is I didn't fully realize how skillfully it was all done until I sat down and started to review the book.</span>
